{{italic title}} {{Infobox artwork | title = A Visit from the Old Mistress | image_file = A_Visit_from_the_Old_Mistress.jpg | painting_alignment = right | image_size = 300px | alt = A meeting between four women; three freed slaves and their former mistress. | medium = [[Oil painting|Oil on canvas]] | artist = [[Winslow Homer]] | year = {{Start date|1876}} | height_metric = | width_metric = | height_imperial = | width_imperial = | condition = On display | city = [[Washington, DC]] | museum = [[Smithsonian Museum of American Art]] | coordinates = <!-- Only use for the exact coordinates of the artwork itself (and only where known) and not for the coordinates of the museum. Leave blank if coordinates are not known. --> | owner = }} '''''A Visit from the Old Mistress''''' is an 1876 painting by American artist [[Winslow Homer]]. It was one of several works that Homer created during a mid-1870s visit to Virginia, where he had served as a war correspondent during the [[American Civil War|Civil War]].<ref name="VA Museum">{{cite journal |last1=Wood |first1=Peter |last2=Dalton |first2=Karen |year=1989 |title=Winslow Homer's images of Blacks: The Civil War and Reconstruction years |journal=Virginia Museum of Fine Arts Bulletin|volume=49 |issue=3 |pages=3–4 |publisher=Virginia Museum of Fine Arts}}</ref> Scholars have noted that the painting's composition is taken from Homer's earlier painting ''Prisoners from the Front,'' which depicts a group of captive Confederate soldiers defiantly regarding a Union officer.<ref name="Calo">{{cite journal |last1=Calo |first1=Mary Ann |year=1980 |title=Winslow Homer's Visits to Virginia during Reconstruction |journal=American Art Journal |volume=12 |issue=1 |pages=4–27 |publisher=Kennedy Galleries Inc. |doi= |url=}}</ref> It, along with Homer's other paintings of black southern life from this period, have been praised as an "invaluable record of an important segment of life in Virginia during the Reconstruction."<ref name="VA Museum"/> {{external media | width = 210px | align = left | headerimage=[[File:Smithtour6.JPG|210px]] | video1 = [https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XMB4I0Rrig8&list=SP7gn_68Hr4h9KzVIeuI0MeMQwK47qKZFi Podcast: The Civil War and American Art, Episode 5], [[Smithsonian American Art Museum]]<ref name="smithvid">{{cite web | title =The Civil War and American Art, Episode 5 | work = | publisher =[[Smithsonian American Art Museum]] | date = | url =https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=XMB4I0Rrig8&list=SP7gn_68Hr4h9KzVIeuI0MeMQwK47qKZFi | accessdate= February 15, 2012}}</ref> }}
