'''''Talking About Detective Fiction''''' is a book written by [[P. D. James]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books/about/Talking_About_Detective_Fiction.html?id=sLTU-IzWQaUC&redir_esc=y|title=Talking About Detective Fiction|last=James|first=P. D.|date=2017-03-26|publisher=Vintage Books|isbn=9780307743138|language=en}}</ref> and published by [[Knopf Doubleday]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://knopfdoubleday.com/2009/12/01/talking-about-detective-fiction-by-p-d-james/|title=Talking About Detective Fiction by P. D. James|website=Knopf Doubleday|access-date=2017-03-26}}</ref> (owned by [[Penguin Random House]]<ref>{{Cite book|url=http://www.penguinrandomhouse.com/books/200851/talking-about-detective-fiction-by-p-d-james/9780307743138/|title=Talking About Detective Fiction by P. D. James {{!}} PenguinRandomHouse.com|language=en-US}}</ref>) on 1 December 2009, which later went on to win the [[Anthony Award]] for Best Critical Non-Fiction in 2010.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.bouchercon.com/anthony-awards/winners-and-nominees/|title=Winners and Nominees|date=2015-08-10|work=Bouchercon|access-date=2017-03-26|language=en}}</ref>
