{{italic title}}
'''''Tiara i korona''''' is a novel by Polish writer [[Teodor Jeske-Choiński]], first published in 1900. Political conflict and religious views are central to the novel which explores the famous dispute between the Emperor [[Henry IV, Holy Roman Emperor|Henry IV]] and [[Pope Gregory VII]].<ref>[http://www.racjonalista.pl/ks.php/k,643 Racjonalista]</ref>

